/// "ABOUT"
@node ABOUT "About fxPAINT"

@{BG fill}@{FG shine}  About fxPAINT@{FG text}@{BG back}
  fxPAINT is the first and only image-processing-software
  for the AMIGA, that makes consequent use of the AMIGA-
  hardware and available extensions (especially PPC-boards).
  That`s why fxPAINT offers you a great functionality and
  flexibility.

  It combines several types of programs and is much more
  than just a traditional painting-package (though it does
  that job, too). You can organise, convert, view your
  pictures, create HTML-overviews or print them. Scan them,
  digitize them, create them .. need a fractal graphic, fire
  or screenshots ? No problem! fxPAINT can even be used as a
  workbench-enhancement!

  No matter whether you are a graphics specialist or a now-and-
  then user, you will be fascinated by the speed, workflow and
  extended abilities of fxPAINT.
@endnode
///
/// "FEATURES"
@node FEATURES "Features"

@{BG fill}@{FG shine}  Features@{FG text}@{BG back}
        · @{b}Support of existing hardware@{ub}
                > Scanner (using RBM`s ScanQuix)
                > VLab (not Motion)
                > graphic tableaus

        · @{b}Creation of new pictures and textures as basic function@{ub}
                > Fractals
                > Fire
                > Screengrabber

        · @{b}Full PPC-Support@{ub}
                > PPC-support was included from the beginning on
                > Support of WarpUP and PowerUP (ppc.lib)
                > Open PPC-support allows support for theoretically every (maybe new) PPC-Driver-System

        · @{b}Optimized printing routines@{ub}
                > Support for TurboPrint
                > Support for old printer.device
                > Support for the new API in AmigaOS 3.5

        · @{b}24 Bit-Alpha-Channel@{ub}
                > Easy usage and choosing
                > Full control over transparency effects
                > aimed changing of red-, green- and blue-compentents of an image

        · @{b}Open and publically documented Plugin-API fxPLUGIN for@{ub}
                > Loader-Modules
                > Saver-Modules
                > Effect-Modules
                > Displaydrivers
                > Modules for additional functionality

        · @{b}Over 70 effects and special effects@{ub}
                > Effects are being calculated and displayed in realtime
                > Effects are sorted by categories (-> find wanted effect fast)

                > Anti "red eyes"
                > Antique
                > Black&White
                > Bluebox
                > Bumpmapper (3D-Logos with shadows, glow, etc)
                > Buttonborder
                > Clone
