///

/// "HOWWORK"
@node HOWWORK "How fxPAINT works"

@{BG fill}@{FG shine}  How fxPAINT works@{FG text}@{BG back}
        In order to understand the whole documentation, you should
        first learn how fxPAINT works:

        @{b}fxPAINT works with several "layers" (from back to front):@{ub}
                - the picture layer
                  This is what you created or loaded into fxPAINT

                - the drawing layer  (8 Bit)
                - the alpha layer   (24 Bit)
                  These two layers are defining the areas, the effect layer
                  replaces the effect layer.

                - the effect layer
                  the effect to be calculated on the image

        @{b}In short:@{ub}
                fxPAINT creates the image by merging the effect layer
                and the picture layer using the data of the drawing
                and alpha-layer.

                In most cases, this is a simple rubthrough, but in
                paint-mode, fxPAINT also uses the drawing- and alpha-
                layer to dynamically calculate the effect layer and
                merge it in.

        @{b}Drawing:@{ub}
                If you draw with fxPAINT, pressing the left mousebutton
                adds, pressing the right mousebuttons removes the effect
                at that position.
@endnode
///

/// "TOOLBOX"
@node TOOLBOX "Toolbox"

@{BG fill}@{FG shine}  Toolbox (@{"Pic" link "Pictures/REF_Toolbox.ilbm/main"})@{FG text}@{BG back}
        The toolbox allows easy access to all the most important tools
        and modules. The icons from left to right, top to bottom:

        · @{"Magic stick" link MAGICSTICK} (1)
          Actives/Deactives the magic stick

        · @{"Drawing tool" link DRAWTOOLS} selection (2)
          Click on this button and keep the mousebutton
          pressed. Now select the drawing tool you want
          to use and release the mousebutton.

        · @{b}Colorpicker@{ub} (3)
          Actives/Deactives the colorpicker. When the color-
          picker is selected, the next click makes the under-
          lying color the current color of the current project.

        · @{"Color manager" link PALETTE} (4)
          Opens the color manager.

        · @{"Effect options" link EFFECTOPTIONS} (5)
          Opens the effect`s options, if any exist.

        · @{"fxMANAGER" link FXMANAGER} (6)
          Opens the fxMANAGER.

        · @{"Brush manager" link BRUSHMANAGER} (7)
          Opens the brush manager.

        · @{"Layer toolbox" link LAYERTOOLBOX} (8)
          Opens the layer toolbox.

        · @{"fxALBUM" link FXALBUM} (9)
          Opens the fxALBUM.

        · @{"Plugin launcher" link PLUGINLAUNCHER} (10)
          Opens the plugin-launcher.

        · @{b}Image-chooser@{ub} (11)
          Click on this button and keep the left mousebutton
          pressed. Now select the image you want to make the
          current and release the left mousebutton.

        · @{b}Alphachannel-chooser@{ub} (12)
          Click on this button and keep the left mousebutton
          pressed. Now select the image you want to make the
          alpha-channel of the current image and release the
          left mousebutton.

        · @{b}Alphachannel active@{ub}  (13)
          If this button is active, the alpha-channel for the
          current image is active.

        · @{b}Fast Pen-chooser@{ub}     (14)
          Click on this button and keep the left mousebutton
          pressed. Now select the pen you want to use for the
          current image and release the left mousebutton.

@endnode
///
/// "TOOLBAR"
@node TOOLBAR "Toolbar"

@{BG fill}@{FG shine}  Toolbar (@{"Pic" link "Pictures/REF_Toolbar.ilbm/main"})@{FG text}@{BG back}
        The toolbar contains mainly shortcuts to whole-image-operations.
        From left to right:

        · Quick @{"create new image" link CREATENEWIMAGE} (1)
          Click on this button and keep the left mousebutton
          pressed. Now select the kind of image creator and
          release the left mousebutton.

        · @{b}@{"Load new image" link LOADIMAGE}@{ub} (2)
          A click on this button pops up an ASL-requester. Choose
          your image and fxPAINT will load it. Also see
          "@{"supported formats" link SUPPORTEDFORMATS}".

        · @{"Save image" link SAVEIMAGE} (3)
          Pops up the save requester. Also see "@{"supported formats" link SUPPORTEDFORMATS}".

        · @{"Print image" link PRINTIMAGE} (4)
          - Pops up the printer requester, if you select the higher image.
          - Sends the image to TurboPrint, if you select the lower image.
            NOTE: TurboPrint has to be installed for this :)

        · @{b}Zoom in@{ub} (5)
          Zooms into the current picture.

        · @{b}Zoom out@{ub} (6)
          Zooms out of the current picture.

        · @{b}Fill layer@{ub} (7)
          Fills the current layer with intensity 255 (the
          effect is fully visible).

        · @{b}Clear layer@{ub} (8)
          Clears the current layer and fills it with intensity 0
          (the effect is fully invisible).

        · @{b}Undo@{ub} (9)
          Undos the last drawn change. You can`t undo fixes or operations,
          that change the size of the picture.

        · @{b}Redo@{ub} (10)
          Redos the last drawn change.

        · @{b}Fix image@{ub} (11)
          Fixes the image (makes all changes un-undoable) and clears the
          layer. If the option "Keep layer" is on in the @{"layer toolbox" link LAYERTOOLBOX},
          the layer is kept.

        · @{b}Iconify@{ub} (12)
          Iconifies the current image to the @{"picture selcection bar" link PICTURESELECTIONBAR}.

        · @{b}Statusline@{ub} (13)
          The statusline shows the currently running operation.

        · @{b}Progressbar@{ub} (14)
          The progressbar shows the progress of the running operation.
@endnode
