///

/// "FAQ"
@node FAQ "Frequently asked questions"

@{BG fill}@{FG shine}  Frequently asked questions@{FG text}@{BG back}
        @{b}Question:@{ub} I have a tableau-driver installed, but fxPAINT does not
                  use the pressure data.
          @{b}Answer:@{ub} There are three possibilities, why this doesn`t work:
                  a) you haven`t enabled tableau-support in the @{"settings" link SETTINGS}.
                  b) your driver does not submit the pressure-data via
                     the documented, systemconform way of AmigaOS 3.x
                     but via a special port-construction
                  c) your driver doesn`t submit the pressure-data at
                     all.

                  If b) is the case and you have the developer documentations,
                  you might want to write a tablett-driver-plugin for fxPAINT.
                  Contact felix@innovative-web.de for details, on how to create
                  one.

                  Known, incompatible drivers:
                        · none

                  Known, compatible drivers:
                        · All drivers available from Haage&Partner/Escena.
                        · WACOM_150.lha
                          @{b}NOTE:@{ub} If fxPAINT shall get the pressure-data, you
                                have to set the tooltype INPUT_EVENT of the
                                driver`s icon (Wacom) in WBStartup to TABLET.
                                If you set PIXEL, the pressure-data won`t be
                                submitted to fxPAINT.

        @{b}Question:@{ub} Why is GIF and LZW-TIFF not supported ?
          @{b}Answer:@{ub} A licence for the LZW-compression-method currently is
                  quite expensive, even if you only wanted to create a freeware
                  loader/saver. It is too expensive (beginning with 5000 US$) to
                  justify a support at this time. However, reading GIF is possible
                  via the GIF-datatype of AmigaOS 3.5 and reading LZW-TIFFs is
                  possible with the datatypes available on Aminet.

        @{b}Question:@{ub} fxPAINT crashes on my WarpUP-system.
          @{b}Answer:@{ub} There are some things you should pay attention to when
                  running fxPAINT under WarpUP:
                        1) Get the latest version of WarpUP installed (V4.0 or
                           later), older versions contain a bug that crash fxPAINT
                           when running under WarpUP.

                        2) Don`t use fxPAINT the way, that you first terminate
                           the ppc.library and then run fxPAINT. This simply won`t
                           work.

                        3) If you`re using ppc.library-Emulation by Frank Wille,
                           please use V0.6d or later, as otherwhise fxPAINT will
                           crash, as it can`t detect the emulation then and uses
                           a ppc.library-version which crashes, because the emulation
                           still isn`t a full implementation.

                        4) The fxWARP.library has to be in LIBS:

                        5) Check our site`s download section for a patch:
                           http://www.innovative-web.de/

        @{b}Question:@{ub} Argh! I don`t get the message of the fire-tutorial!!
          @{b}Answer:@{ub} Switch to fxPAINTCD:Graphics/Videos/ and double-click
                  on fire_ws.avi to see how it works.

        @{b}Question:@{ub} I`m using Picasso96 and the GUI looks "a bit" strange.
          @{b}Answer:@{ub} Picasso96 has a bug in its CyberGraphX-emulation. Activate
                  the workaround in the @{"settings" link SETTINGS} and don`t use
                  the option "Use CGX curiosity".

        @{b}Question:@{ub} BUG! BUG! I can choose from the menus but they don`t react!!
          @{b}Answer:@{ub} You`re most likely using MagicMenu. This hack doesn`t have a
                  proper implementation of the LendMenus()-command of intuition.library.
                  You will notice, that the shortcuts (which are basically the same
                  as if you would use the pulldown-menu) are still intact and working for
                  all windows - they have not been patched by MagicMenu. Maybe the author
                  of MagicMenu adds support for this command in his next version released.

        @{b}Question:@{ub} I didn`t find an answer to a question here. What shall I
                  do now ?
          @{b}Answer:@{ub} Please check the FAQs at http://www.innovative-web.de/
                  on the fxPAINT-homepage (you get there from the products page).
                  If you didn`t find an answer, @{"contact" link CONTACT} us (EMail is prefered).
@endnode
///

/// "HINTSNTIPS"
@node HINTSNTIPS "Hints & Tips"

@{BG fill}@{FG shine}  Hints & Tips@{FG text}@{BG back}
        · @{"How to speedup fxPAINT" link HINTS_SPEEDUP}
        · @{"Keep the plugins-dir up-to-date" link HINTS_UPTODATE}
@endnode

@node HINTS_SPEEDUP "How to speedup fxPAINT"

@{BG fill}@{FG shine}  How to speedup fxPAINT@{FG text}@{BG back}
        fxPAINT already is very fast, but you can speed it up
        even more, if you configure it correctly:

        · @{b}The display routines@{ub}
          > CyberGraphX (CGX) has a quite strange feature. Everyone who
            already had a look at the autodocs of CyberGraphX might have
            pointed out, that there are different functions for scaled and
            immediately rendered 24bit-data (ScalePixelArray) and for direct
            output without scaling (WritePixelArray). If you now believe,
            that scaling needs more time, you`re wrong - at least for the
            CV 64/3D. So if you check the "CGX Curiosity"-checkbox in the
            @{"Settings" link SETTINGS}, fxPAINT will use the scaling routine without scaling
            instead of the direct output. To get the best performance for
            your graphics-board, check, whether that curiosity exists for
            your board, too.

        · @{b}The GUI@{ub}
          > fxPAINT`s GUI is unique under the AMIGA`s programs. However,
            drawing such a GUI also needs a minimal amount of time. If you
            don`t need 24Bit-gradients, you can switch off "fxGUI-Effects"
            in the @{"Settings" link SETTINGS}.

        · @{b}The CPU(s)@{ub}
          > Optimize the PPC-Merge-Barrier. See @{"Settings" link SETTINGS}.
          > Install an optimized version for your 68K-CPU.
          > Make sure, two binaries are in fxPAINT`s subdirectory PPC,
            if you have a PPC.
          > Under WarpUP, fxPAINT is a little bit slower. This is not a
            disadvantage of WarpUP, which works at least as fast as the
            ppc.lib or even faster, but of vbcc, with which fxPAINT for
            WarpUP was compiled. However, speed might improve under WarpUP
            in future, when another compiler is used.
@endnode

@node HINTS_UPTODATE "Keep the plugin-directory up-to-date"

@{BG fill}@{FG shine}  Keep the plugin-directory up-to-date@{FG text}@{BG back}
        In order to get the best out of fxPAINT and your AMIGA, keep
        the contents of your plugin-directory up-to-date. A special
        Plugin-Page with links to all available Plugins for fxPAINT
        can be found on our website at http://www.innovative-web.de/:

                · First click on the AMIGA-Logo
                · Click on "Products"
                · Click on the fxPAINT-Logo
                · Select "Plugins" from the navigation-bar
                  on top.
@endnode
